---
// Drop into: <astro-project>/src/pages/taptallypro/privacy.astro
// Public URL: /taptallypro/privacy
import TapTallyProLayout from '../../layouts/TapTallyProLayout.astro';
---
<TapTallyProLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Tap Tally Pro"
  description="Tap Tally Pro is a privacy-friendly multi-counter app. We do not collect any personal data."
>
  <main>
    <p class="eyebrow">Tap Tally Pro</p>
    <h1>Privacy<span class="dot">.</span></h1>
    <p class="muted"><small>Effective date: 2026-05-06</small></p>

    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <p>Tap Tally Pro is designed to be private by default. The app does not collect personal data, does not require an account, and does not transmit any user-generated content to our servers — because we don't have any.</p>

    <h2>Data we collect</h2>
    <p>None. Tap Tally Pro does not collect personal information, usage analytics, or behavioral data. There is no account, no login, no email signup. Your taps are your taps.</p>

    <h2>Data stored on your device</h2>
    <p>Your counters, preferences, tap history, and settings are stored locally on your device using Apple's frameworks: <span class="mono">SwiftData</span>, <span class="mono">UserDefaults</span>, and <span class="mono">FileManager</span>. Uninstalling the app removes this data. We have no copy.</p>

    <h2>In-app purchases</h2>
    <p>Tap Tally Pro offers a one-time unlock purchase processed by Apple via StoreKit. Apple handles all payment information. We never see your card number, billing address, or Apple ID. We only receive a transaction receipt confirming entitlement.</p>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <p>None. Tap Tally Pro uses only Apple-provided frameworks (SwiftUI, SwiftData, StoreKit). We do not integrate any third-party analytics, advertising, crash reporting, or tracking SDKs.</p>

    <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
    <p>Tap Tally Pro is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. The app contains no advertising and no user-generated content sharing.</p>

    <h2>Permissions</h2>
    <p>Tap Tally Pro does not request any sensitive permissions: no camera, microphone, location, contacts, photos, notifications, or health data. The app uses haptic feedback (which does not require permission) and that is all.</p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy as the app evolves. The effective date above will reflect the most recent change. Continued use of the app after a change means you accept the updated policy.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For questions about this policy, email <a href="mailto:witchaudiodev@gmail.com">witchaudiodev@gmail.com</a>.</p>

    <footer>
      <p>Tap Tally Pro is developed by nocodehuman. <a href="/taptallypro/support">Support</a> · <a href="/taptallypro">About</a></p>
    </footer>
  </main>
</TapTallyProLayout>
